  '{"verdicts":{"C1":"accept","C2":"accept","C3":"accept","C4":"reject","C5":"reject","C6":"reject","C7":"reject"},"ranking":["C1","C2","C3"],"explanations":{"C1":"Best comp — same sub, same era, only 35 SF less GLA, arm''s length 2 mo. ago. Minimal adjustments needed.","C2":"Strong comp — adjacent neighborhood, similar era and quality. Minor GLA (+35 SF) and bath (2 vs 1.5) adjustments needed.","C3":"Good comp — same sub. Seller concession and half-bath adjustments required.","C4":"Reject — condominium unit vs single-family residence. Different property type, ownership structure, HOA considerations, and buyer pool.","C5":"Reject — court-confirmed estate sale is typically not arm''s length. Executor may lack full market knowledge and have motivations other than price maximization.","C6":"Reject — 19 months old; exceeds the 12-month guideline. Time adjustment would not reliably reflect current market conditions.","C7":"Reject — sold as-is with condition unverifiable at time of sale. USPAP requires adequate data verification; an unverifiable condition comp is unreliable."},"justification":"C1, C2, C3 are all similar-era ranch homes of matching quality — critical for FHA comparability. C1 (same sub, 35 SF less, no concessions) is strongest; C2 (adjacent neighborhood, minor bath/GLA adj); C3 (same sub, concession + half-bath adj). C4 rejected — condo vs SFR, different property type. C5 — court-confirmed estate sale, not arm''s length. C6 — 19 months old. C7 — sold as-is, condition unverifiable, fails USPAP data verification standard."}'::jsonb,
